  "editor.panel.narrative_intro.title": "Narrative Workspace",
  "editor.panel.narrative_intro.heading": "Sub-phase 2.5 — Game systems (in progress)",
  "editor.panel.narrative_intro.body": "This workspace is the home of the upcoming game-content editors: Dialog Editor, Quest Editor, and Inventory. Right now you're seeing the Node Graph Sandbox — the foundation infrastructure that the Dialog and Quest editors will be built on top of. Use it to test the framework (pan/zoom, sockets, connections, undo, save/load) but be aware: this is plumbing, not a final tool.",
  "editor.panel.narrative_intro.roadmap_header": "Roadmap (next hitos)",
  "editor.panel.narrative_intro.item_dialog": "Dialog Editor (F2H47): each node = a line spoken by an NPC. Connections = options the player picks. Wire it to a NPC in your scene via a DialogComponent that points to a .mooddialog file you'll build visually here.",
  "editor.panel.narrative_intro.item_quest": "Quest Editor: each node = an objective. Connections = dependencies. Quests trigger from world events (entering an area, picking up an item, killing an enemy tag).",
  "editor.panel.narrative_intro.item_inventory": "Inventory (separate UI, not node-graph): item asset browser with 3D preview + grid/list/equipment-slot component you attach to entities. Pickup/drop wired to physics triggers + the HUD interact prompt.",
  "editor.panel.narrative_intro.footer": "All three systems are engine-grade primitives: data-driven (.mooddialog/.moodquest/.mooditem assets), no hardcoded gameplay semantics, Lua hooks for game logic. They serve any genre.",

